  Determinan $A = (2)(3) - (1)(4) = 6 - 4 = 2$.
  Determinan $B = (1)(2) - (-1)(0) = 2$.
  Perkalian matriks $AB = \begin{pmatrix} 2(1)+1(0) & 2(-1)+1(2) \\ 4(1)+3(0) & 4(-1)+3(2) \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & 0 \\ 4 & 2 \end{pmatrix}$.
  Sifat determinan $\det(AB) = \det(A) \times \det(B) = 2 \times 2 = 4$.
