  $\sin 120^\circ = \sin(180^\circ-60^\circ) = \frac{1}{2}\sqrt{3}$.
  $\cos 120^\circ = \cos(180^\circ-60^\circ) = -\frac{1}{2}$.
  $\cos 300^\circ = \cos(360^\circ-60^\circ) = \frac{1}{2}$.
  Pembilang: $\frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{2}\sqrt{3}$.
  Penyebut: $-\frac{1}{2} - \frac{1}{2} = -1$.
  Hasil: $\frac{0.5 + 0.5\sqrt{3}}{-1} = -\frac{1}{2} - \frac{1}{2}\sqrt{3}$.
